1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with rate performance and interference in a multiuser MIMO broadcast channel, which are key topics in information theory.
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a novel framework for transmission in FDD massive MIMO systems, which is relevant to networking and internet architecture.
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses power allocation and system parameters, which are related to systems and control.
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with transmission of messages in a multiuser MIMO broadcast channel, which can be considered as a form of multimedia transmission.
5. cs.COM (Computational Complexity) - Although not a major focus of the paper, the analysis and optimization of the proposed framework may involve computational complexity considerations.
